title: Naas North
text:
Naas North () is a <a href="Barony%20%28Ireland%29">barony</a> in <a href="County%20Kildare">County Kildare</a>, <a href="Republic%20of%20Ireland">Republic of Ireland</a>.
Etymology.
Naas North derives its name from the town of <a href="Naas">Naas</a> (Irish "Nás na Ríogh", "assembly-place of the kings").
Location.
Naas North barony is located in northeast <a href="County%20Kildare">County Kildare</a>, south and east of the <a href="River%20Liffey">Liffey</a>.
History.
These were part of the ancient lands of the <a href="U%C3%AD%20Broin">Uí Broin</a> (O'Byrnes) before the 13th century, retaken in the 14th. The Uí Ceallaig Cualann (O'Kelly) were also noted early in the eastern section. An Uí Fhionáin (O'Finan) sept is noted in the north part of this barony. There was originally a single Naas barony, divided into north and <a href="Naas%20South">south</a> baronies before 1603.
